{"type":"message","id":"6ea3e65f","parentId":"b64a6197","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:39:29.942Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse is still running. Let me wait for it to complete and read the most recent log file.","thinkingSignature":"aba818f77aeac67406bcf07b4ab3417382a6ce6a2be24d341edffdcdff6a38dd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kk2x60pvtjct_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"gentle-mist","timeout":45000}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kk2x60pvtjct_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 013710.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":398,"output":119,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12471,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774330763847}}
{"type":"message","id":"dd9fe2a5","parentId":"6ea3e65f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:39:52.435Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kk2x60pvtjct_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5366\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1374\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 013914 - The TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression) is the critical next step to unify Phase 1 and Phase 2. The classifier needs to analyze pulse logs and identify invariant vs variant content, then test prediction accuracy.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"gentle-mist","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5366\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1374\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 013914 - The TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression) is the critical next step to unify Phase 1 and Phase 2. The classifier needs to analyze pulse logs and identify invariant vs variant content, then test prediction accuracy.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774330792432}}
{"type":"message","id":"366a909c","parentId":"dd9fe2a5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:39:52.437Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kk2x60pvtjct_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 013710\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state, I need to advance the Phase 1 goal of implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The pending action is to implement the TIC classifier on pulse log files.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what needs to be done:\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC implementation that:\r\n- Reads pulse logs from the logs/ directory\r\n- Classifies content as invariant (persists across pulses) vs variant (changes)\r\n- Tests prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me first check what pulse logs exist and their format.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending TIC experiment, I need to implement the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier to test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure. Let me first examine the available pulse logs to understand the data format.\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs, then tests next-pulse prediction. I need to create the implementation framework first.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment implementation that will analyze pulse logs for invariants, test classification accuracy, and validate next-pulse prediction against the success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nPULSE_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_blocks(pulse_file):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract distinct content blocks from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n    blocks = []\r\n    # Split by headers and major sections\r\n    sections = re.split(r'\\n(?=##|# |### )', content)\r\n    for section in sections:\r\n        section = section.strip()\r\n        if section and len(section) > 20:\r\n            blocks.append(section)\r\n    return blocks\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulse_files):\r\n    \"\"\"Find content that appears across multiple pulses = invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    all_blocks = []\r\n    for pf in pulse_files:\r\n        blocks = extract_content_blocks(pf)\r\n        all_blocks.append(set(blocks))\r\n    \r\n    if not all_blocks:\r\n        return set(), set()\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant: appears in >= 50% of pulses\r\n    frequency = Counter()\r\n    for blocks in all_blocks:\r\n        for block in blocks:\r\n            frequency[block] += 1\r\n    \r\n    threshold = len(all_blocks) * 0.5\r\n    invariants = {b for b, count in frequency.items() if count >= threshold}\r\n    variants = {b for b, count in frequency.items() if count < threshold}\r\n    \r\n    return invariants, variants\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulse_file, invariants, variants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    blocks = extract_content_blocks(pulse_file)\r\n    classified = {'invariant': [], 'variant': []}\r\n    for block in blocks:\r\n        if block in invariants:\r\n            classified['invariant'].append(block)\r\n        elif block in variants:\r\n            classified['variant'].append(block)\r\n    return classified\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(training_pulses, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content from invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    # Invariants should persist into next pulse\r\n    # Extract \"pending actions\" and \"goals\" from invariants as predictors\r\n    predictions = []\r\n    for inv in invariants:\r\n        if any(kw in inv.lower() for kw in ['pending', 'next', 'action', 'goal']):\r\n            predictions.append(inv)\r\n    return predictions\r\n\r\ndef evaluate_tic(pulse_files):\r\n    \"\"\"Run full TIC experiment evaluation.\"\"\"\r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 3:\r\n        print(f\"ERROR: Need >= 3 pulses, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return None\r\n    \r\n    # Split: first 80% for training, last 20% for testing\r\n    split_idx = int(len(pulse_files) * 0.8)\r\n    training = pulse_files[:split_idx]\r\n    test = pulse_files[split_idx:]\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"Training pulses: {len(training)}, Test pulses: {len(test)}\")\r\n    \r\n    # Phase 1: Extract invariants from training\r\n    invariants, variants = extract_invariants(training)\r\n    print(f\"Invariants found: {len(invariants)}, Variants: {len(variants)}\")\r\n    \r\n    # Phase 2: Classify test pulses\r\n    correct = 0\r\n    total = 0\r\n    for tp in test:\r\n        classified = classify_content(tp, invariants, variants)\r\n        # Ground truth: compare to training pulse baseline\r\n        train_classified = classify_content(training[0], invariants, variants)\r\n        # Count matches\r\n        for block in classified['invariant']:\r\n            if block in train_classified['invariant']:\r\n                correct += 1\r\n            total += 1\r\n        for block in classified['variant']:\r\n            if block in train_classified['variant']:\r\n                correct += 1\r\n            total += 1\r\n    \r\n    classification_accuracy = (correct / total * 100) if total > 0 else 0\r\n    print(f\"Classification accuracy: {classification_accuracy:.1f}%\")\r\n    \r\n    # Phase 3: Next-pulse prediction\r\n    predictions = predict_next_pulse(training, invariants)\r\n    prediction_hits = 0\r\n    if predictions and len(test) > 1:\r\n        next_pulse =\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:37:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774330792435}}
